The '''geology of Eritrea''' in east [[Africa]] broadly consists of [[Precambrian]] rocks in the west, [[Paleozoic]] glacial sedimentary rocks in the South and [[Cenozoic]] [[sedimentary rocks|sediments]] and [[volcanic rocks|volcanics]] along the coastal zone adjoining the [[Red Sea]]. The Precambrian rocks been involved with the orogeny process, which is when a section of the Earth's crust is deformed to form a mountain range. Mesozoic sediments in the [[Danakil Alps|Danakil]] and Aysha horsts, which are raised blocks of the Earth's crust that have been lifted, were deformed.<ref name= "geoatlas" /> The older rocks include [[metamorphic rocks|meta-sediments]] and older [[gneiss]]ic [[basement (geology)|basement]] belonging to different [[Proterozoic]] [[terrane]]s. [[Mesozoic]] sediments of marine origin occur in the coastal area along the Red Sea. A number of thin [[Miocene]] age [[basalt]] flows occur within the sediments of this zone whilst the basalts of the [[Aden Series]] date from [[Pliocene]] to [[Holocene]] times, some being extruded at the time of a major phase of uplift and rifting during the [[Pleistocene]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eisourcebook.org/1419_Geology.html|title=Eritrea, geology Extractive Industries Source Book|access-date=October 19, 2016|website=Extractive Industries|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130704003945/http://www.eisourcebook.org/1419_Geology.html|archivedate=July 4, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eisourcebook.org/cms/Jan%202013/Eritrea,%20Simplified%20Geological%20Map.jpg|title=Eritrea, geological map Extractive Industries Source Book|website=Extractive Industries|access-date=October 19, 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304140153/http://www.eisourcebook.org/cms/Jan%202013/Eritrea%2C%20Simplified%20Geological%20Map.jpg|archivedate=March 4, 2016|df=}}</ref>

==Economic geology==
The country produces [[salt]], [[gypsum]] and [[kaolin]] but also has resources of [[asbestos]], [[baryte]], [[potash]] and [[talc]]. Metal resources include [[copper]], [[gold]], [[iron ore]], [[lead]], [[zinc]], [[silver]] and [[magnesium]]. There have been discoveries of high-grade polymetallic [[volcanogenic massive sulfide ore deposit]]s in recent years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eisourcebook.org/1417_Mining.html|title=Eritrea, mining Extractive Industries Source Book|access-date=October 19, 2016|website=Extractive Industries}}</ref> Most mineral production in the south of the country was eliminated due to tension from ongoing conflicts with Ethiopia. About {{convert|500|kg|lb|abbr=on}} of gold was mined annually in the late 1990s.<ref name="geoatlas">{{cite book|last=Schlüter|first=Thomas|title=Geological Atlas of Africa: With Notes on Stratigraphy, Tectonics, Economic Geology, Geohazards, Geosites and Geoscientific Education of Each Country|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|url={{Google books|IfvKWpsISTQC|page=88|plainurl=yes}}|access-date=October 18, 2016|date=April 19, 2008}}</ref>{{rp|96}}

In the Dallol depression, large quantities of Neogene evaporites can be found, including halites, gypsym, and potassium salt.<ref name="geoatlas" />{{rp|96}}

