{{Redirect|Space fleet|the Games Workshop board game|Space Fleet|other uses|Space Force (disambiguation)}} {{Use American English|date=June 2018}}
A '''space force''' is a [[military branch]] that conducts [[space warfare]]. Currently, one [[Sovereign state|country]] has previously had an independent space force. The [[Russian Space Forces]] was an independent organization that existed from 1992 to 1997 and from 2001 to 2011; it was reestablished in 2015 as a branch of the [[Russian Aerospace Forces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.defensenews.com/global/europe/2018/06/21/as-trump-pushes-for-separate-space-force-russia-moves-fast-the-other-way/|title=As Trump pushes for separate space force, Russia moves fast the other way|first=Matthew|last=Bodner|date=22 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref> A space force is almost always a part of the [[air force]], which may function as an air and space force or as an aerospace force, as the [[United States Air Force]] does.<ref>"[http://www.afspc.af.mil/About-Us/ About Us]". ''Air Force Space Command''.</ref><ref>Moorehead, Richard D. (July–August 2004). "[http://www.au.af.mil/au/awc/awcgate/milreview/moorhead.pdf Will We Need a Space Force?]" ''Military Review''. p. 50–53.</ref><ref>Moncrief, William S. (Winter/Spring 2010). "[https://web.archive.org/web/20130215225119/http://www.smdc-armyforces.army.mil/Pic_Archive/ASJ_PDFs/ASJ_VOL_9_NO_1_010.pdf Building a United States Space Force]". ''Army Space Journal''. p. 34–38. Archived from [http://www.smdc-armyforces.army.mil/Pic_Archive/ASJ_PDFs/ASJ_VOL_9_NO_1_010.pdf the original] on February 15, 2013.</ref>
In an announcement on June 18, 2018, U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] proposed the establishment of the [[United States Space Force]] as the sixth branch of the [[United States Armed Forces|U.S. Armed Forces]].<ref>"[https://www.abc15.com/news/trump-says-pentagon-directed-to-launch-space-force-branch-of-military Space Force and Air Force will be 'separate but equal' branches". ''[[CNN]]''. [[KNXV-TV]]. June 18, 2018. Retrieved June 18, 2018.</ref> On August 9, 2018, United States Vice President Mike Pence announced a plan to create the proposed service by 2020.<ref>"[https://www.cnbc.com/2018/08/09/pence-unveils-plan-for-congress-to-create-space-force-by-2020.html]". ''[[CNBC]]''. August 9, 2018. Retrieved August 9, 2018.</ref>
